    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>NOVARTIS PROFIT RISES 12%</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Novartis AG reports 12 percent rise in net income for first half of year; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The third-largest drug manufacturer in Europe, Novartis A.G. of Switzerland, reported a 12 percent rise in net income for the first half of the year, attributing the growth partly to a pickup in sales of Diovan, a hypertension treatment. The company said profit jumped to 4.19 billion Swiss francs, or $2.43 billion, from 3.74 billion Swiss francs a year earlier. Novartis warned that it expected a slower third quarter than initially expected.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin (NYT)</p>
      </block>
